 | doi =10.1556/SocEc.34.2012.3.8
 | issn = 1588-970X
| accessdate = Sep 10, 2015 }}</ref> The community in Tauranga invited the Bahá'ís to join their interfaith council.<ref>{{cite news
| author=Ruth Keber 
 | title =Interfaith council gets under way with prayers for world peace
 | newspaper =Bay of Plenty Times
 | location =Tauranga, New Zealand
