'''Gwalipa''' was an Indian hermit-saint who lived during the 8th century AD.  According to legend, Gwalipa cured the [[Rajput]] chieftain [[Suraj Sen (Gwalior)|Suraj Sen]] of leprosy, and in gratitude, [[Suraj Sen (Gwalior)|Suraj Sen]] founded the city of [[Gwalior]] in his name.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=ifgtAAAAMAAJ&q=gwalipa&dq=gwalipa&pgis=1 William Curtis, Fodor, Eugene, 1905 ''Fodor's India'' D. McKay., 1971]</ref>

